                     <interp inst="def1-1349-18420404" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">EDWARD REDMAN</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18420404-1349-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18420404-1349-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18420404-1349-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>for stealing, on the <rs id="t18420404-cd-201" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420404-1349-offence-1 t18420404-cd-201"></join>6th of April</rs>, 1 pair of mittens, value 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 1 purse, value 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; 3 sovereigns, 1 half-crown, and 6 shillings; the property of <persName id="t18420404-name-1199" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1199" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1199" type="surname" value="HENSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1199" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420404-1349-offence-1 t18420404-name-1199"></join>Thomas Henson</persName>, from the person of <persName id="t18420404-name-1200" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1200" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1200" type="surname" value="HENSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1200" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420404-1349-offence-1 t18420404-name-1200"></join>Mary Ann Henson</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420404-name-1201" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1201" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1201" type="surname" value="HENSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1201" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN HENSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Thomas Henson. On the 6th of April I went to the Adelaide Gallery, Lowther-arcade, in the Strand. I felt somebody touch me slightly, I turned round immediately, and saw the prisoner going down the long room, rather quickly—I immediately drew my glove, felt in my pocket, and missed my purse—I followed him, and as soon as he got to the end of the room, I said, "You have got my purse"—he said nothing, but endeavoured to get away—I succeeded in catching hold of his coat, and he dragged me down the stairs—I still held him, till assistance came, and the moment assistance came he threw a blue and black striped purse over the bannisters—it was brought up to me soon after, and it was mine—it contained three sovereigns, a pair of black mittens, and 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. or 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. in silver.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CHARNOCK</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> I suppose a great many people were listening to the Infant Sappho? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I only charged the prisoner with the robbery—there was another, but I passed him—I followed the prisoner—I did not collar the other man—the prisoner had got down a few stairs, and I caught hold of him—I can scarcely tell which went</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184204040207"></xptr>
               <p>down stairs first, for I was black from my shoulder to my wrist in the scuffle—I was watching him, and calling for assistance as he was endea<lb></lb>vouring to get away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420404-name-1202" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1202" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1202" type="surname" value="GILLARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1202" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM GILLARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I was at the gallery, and saw a purse come from the prisoner—I do not know whether this is it—I took it from a servant girl, and gave it to the officer—I saw the prisoner throw it down on the ground.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420404-name-1203" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1203" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1203" type="surname" value="KING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1203" type="given" value="LUCY"></interp>LUCY KING</persName>
                  </hi>. I picked the purse up, and gave it to Gillard, who gave it to the policeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420404-name-1204" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1204" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1204" type="surname" value="PARTRIDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1204" type="given" value="JAMES TORRINGTON"></interp>JAMES TORRINGTON PARTRIDGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I watched the prisoner, as I saw four of them together, about eight o'clock, in the lower part of the gallery—I did not know any of the four before, but I had reason to suspect them, I as heard two of them say, "You work below, and we will work up stairs; I will meet you in an hour."</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
